b'Setbacks are brutal and come in many forms. Perseverance thru setbacks can open doors that once never existed.'
b'If you feel you have \xe2\x80\x9cpeaked\xe2\x80\x9d, then you have.'
b'What we have will come and go, who we are is with us always.'
b'Others will try to estimate your worth. You must clearly define your values.'

b'Life is rarely balanced. Many of us chase it but the scales only seem to stay even for moments. Persevere and grow from the hardships, learn to enjoy the highlights and keep chasing those moments of clarity with the universe.'
b'Work hard to make sure kindness is not transactional.'
b'Be gracious and courageous enough to always extend your hand. Be aware enough to adjust it accordingly.'
b'Be grateful not hateful.'

b'Often we drink from wells we didn\xe2\x80\x99t dig, warm ourselves by fires we didn\xe2\x80\x99t start. Appreciate what others have done for us to be where we are. Selflessness or Selfishness are roads we can follow. One is paved by kindness and care, the other by disdain and pride. Choose wisely.'

b'Each day will put forth its challenges. Many of them will not be pleasant. How we react to them is up to us. Summon whatever we can to react with a clear mind, kindness, respect, and understanding.'
b'Behind every superhero is a team that is doing all the hard work. #PEACEMAKER https://t.co/ROAFaFCTYr'
b'Worry less about looking cool in the eyes of others and more about being cool with who you really are.'

b'Those who\xe2\x80\x99ve betrayed my trust have been my biggest failures. Those who have honored my trust have been my biggest successes. I\xe2\x80\x99m grateful for ALL and learn every step of the way.'
b'No need to seek the uncomfortable but no need to run from it. Challenge yourself to build the strength and support to lean in when called upon.'
b'Put forth honest effort not just to do good but to be good.'
b'Be brave enough to push your limits, this way you can find them and then invest the effort to redefine them.'
b'Be kind whenever possible and patient when kindness isn\xe2\x80\x99t available.'

b'The unfamiliar can be very intimidating. Feeling out of place, misunderstood, less than..among others. Ask questions, learn from those more experienced, don\xe2\x80\x99t pretend to know it all, adjust to the environment. Leaning into the unfamiliar can lead to valuable wisdom.'
b'Here\xe2\x80\x99s to the next adventure, whatever it will be and whatever it yields.'
b'Our accomplishments do not serve as a vehicle to treat people poorly. Achievements are simply a gateway to more opportunities.'
b'In complicated times try and focus on making one great choice. Then move on to the next obstacle. One by one, things might get less complicated.'
b'Think of other people. Think of other places. Think other perspectives. Think.'

b'If given an opportunity and you choose to take it, especially in times where opportunities are heavily diminished, give it your best, be accountable for your choices, and be grateful. With so many suffering, complaining thru success may not be the best choice.'

b'Adjusting to any \xe2\x80\x9cuncomfortable\xe2\x80\x9d is stressful, frustrating, and definitely a learning curve. Be mindful through challenging times that many others are fighting thru their own set of problems as well. Kindness, tolerance, and patience take extra work, but have a huge impact.'

b'If given the opportunity to create, be bold. Understand you will not please everyone and criticism is a natural response to putting yourself out there. Don\xe2\x80\x99t create for any other reason than you\xe2\x80\x99ve been given the opportunity to do so, embrace the entire process and it\xe2\x80\x99s lessons'

b'Frustration and unrest can come easily when the future is unclear. Don\xe2\x80\x99t be afraid to talk to those you love and trust. Sometimes just putting thoughts out in the universe, and having someone listen, can subdue stress tremendously.'
b'Do things for the reward of doing them. Any reward after that is a bonus.'

b'Crisis and uncertainty are breeding grounds for panic. We all have feelings and need to recognize them good, or bad. But especially thru unrest, our brains, and logical thought will be our strongest ally.'

b'We evolve everyday. Continue to be curious about who you become. Keep the same curiosity for those relationships you hold dear. If you think you fully know someone, you might not be trying hard enough.'
b'You have 1440 minutes each day to choose who and what gets your attention.'
b'Embrace the deal. And at the same time, keep track of your deal.'
b'We tend to be nicer when we are not mean.'

b'When was the last time you had a real conversation with someone who had an opposing view? Blocking, interrupting, banning, not listening to anyone who may oppose your viewpoint doesn\xe2\x80\x99t \xe2\x80\x9cwin\xe2\x80\x9d a discussion, it prevents one.'
b'Control the controllable. The disorder of others is only your chaos if you make it so.'
b'Don\xe2\x80\x99t let a failed plan ruin the rest of your day. Take it in. Take a moment. Regroup. Refocus, and move forward the best you can.'
b'In any relationship do not try to change someone to be the best them for you. Be the best you for your relationship and find those that love you because of it.'

b'Compete each day with you. Looking at the lives of others can be interesting but can also severely eat away at self worth. Be your best you. Don\xe2\x80\x99t get hung up on what someone else \xe2\x80\x9chas\xe2\x80\x9d or \xe2\x80\x9cdoes\xe2\x80\x9d. Use that energy for you.'

b'All of us have problems and facing them is tough. Let\xe2\x80\x99s try our best to face issues as soon as they\xe2\x80\x99re discovered. Making excuses, shifting blame, or projecting a \xe2\x80\x9cperfect life\xe2\x80\x9d will just lead to deeper problems. Ask for help, be honest, do the work, and the result will be growth'
b'Do your best to learn something each day. Anything, even if it\xe2\x80\x99s something about yourself or your surroundings. As time passes, you won\xe2\x80\x99t get younger, but you can get wiser.'
b'Don\xe2\x80\x99t let those who want to manipulate you forge who you are.'
b'Trying to help someone and trying to change someone are two different things. One can be highly rewarding to most all involved, the other can be self centered, controlling, and destructive.'

b'Love that lasts takes work. Tremendous work. Anyone who thinks differently has little perspective of the timeline and totality of existence. Don\xe2\x80\x99t fear love, but do not ignorantly proceed in thinking it comes without effort.'

b'Be brave enough to embrace humility. The reward will be confidence.'
